    <abstract id="aspace_9b192511cdf5ba98b961f9752d33677f" label="Abstract">Edward Eliscu (1902-1998) was a lyricist, playwright, screenwriter, and a progressive activist in the entertainment industry, notably in Hollywood in the 1930s and 1940s. The collection includes his correspondence, scripts, speeches, articles and photographs.</abstract>
